OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FSaudi court orders first   
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fnaming of man guilty of    
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fsexual harassment          
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, A court in Saudi Arabia has for the    
OL,6, first time ordered that a man convicted
OL,7, of sexual harassment be named and      
OL,8, shamed in public, local media report.  
OL,10,FYasser al-Arawi was found guilty by the
OL,11,FCriminal Court in Medina of harassing a
OL,12,Fwoman using obscene remarks.           
OL,14,FHe was sentenced to eight months in    
OL,15,Fprison and fined $1,330 (#980).        
OL,17,FThe anti-harassment law was amended a  
OL,18,Fyear ago to allow for offenders' names 
OL,19,Fand sentences to be published in local 
OL,20,Fnewspapers at their own expense.       
